# Implement GitHub API rate limiting and backoff



## Requirements

- [ ] Implement rate limiting and backoff strategy for GitHub API calls
- [ ] Parse `X-RateLimit-Remaining` and `X-RateLimit-Reset` headers from responses
- [ ] Use exponential backoff (2^n seconds) with jitter for retries
- [ ] Cache rate limit state in Cachex to avoid redundant API calls when exhausted
- [ ] Respect GitHub's two rate limit tiers: primary (5000 req/hr) and secondary (no burst)
- [ ] Add `with_retry/3` wrapper function for API calls with backoff
- [ ] Support configurable max retries and retry delays
- [ ] Log rate limit state changes (exhausted, reset)
- [ ] Fail fast when rate limit exhausted rather than hammering API

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Rate limit headers parsed correctly from API responses
- [ ] Cachex cache stores remaining/reset-time per authenticated identity
- [ ] `Client.with_retry/3` implements exponential backoff (2^retry_count * base_delay)
- [ ] Jitter added to prevent thundering herd (Â±20% variation)
- [ ] Max retry count configurable (default: 3)
- [ ] Waits until reset time when limit exhausted before retrying
- [ ] Secondary rate limit respected (1 request per second, concurrent limit)
- [ ] Clear logging of retry attempts and rate limit hits
- [ ] Tests verify backoff timing, cache behavior, header parsing
- [ ] Integrates with existing Client module functions
